Thought: I need to write a Ruby function that checks whether a given number is prime. A prime number is greater than 1 and has no divisors other than 1 and itself. I'll implement a function that handles edge cases (numbers <= 1) and checks divisibility up to the square root of the number for efficiency.

```ruby
def prime?(n)
  return false if n <= 1
  return true if n == 2
  return false if n.even?

  (3..Math.sqrt(n)).step(2) do |i|
    return false if n % i == 0
  end
  true
end
```
